A @southwestair Boeing 737 on short final for Baltimoreâ€™s runway 33L after an hour long flight from Nashville operating as WN1073. Recently, Southwest announced that they would be updating their Rapid Reward program, allowing any customer who accumulates points with the airline to never have them expire. It used to be that Southwest points would expire after 24 months of inactivity. Southwest also updated the amount of points needed to receive a Companion Pass from 110,000 to 125,000 points accumulated in a single year. The Companion Pass allows the holder to fly another passenger with them for free.
